advisories.title: Symphony Vulnerable to PHP Code Injection via YAML Parsing
advisories.description: The `Yaml::parse` function in Symfony 2.0.x before 2.0.22 remote attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code via a PHP file, a different vulnerability than CVE-2013-1397.

advisories.title: Symfony Arbitrary PHP code Execution
advisories.description: Symfony 2.0.x before 2.0.22, 2.1.x before 2.1.7, and 2.2.x remote attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code via a serialized PHP object to the (1) Yaml::parse or (2) Yaml\Parser::parse function, a different vulnerability than CVE-2013-1348.
